ethnologue_comment.comment:
Norra [nrr], is listed in E16/E17/E18/E19/E20/E21/E22/E23/E24/E25/E26 as a Nungish language of Northern Myanmar
(no more precise location) with the dialects Nora, Byabe,
Kizolo. The information almost certainly derives from
**hh:hv:VoegelinVoegelin:LW:76**:15, but
**hh:hv:VoegelinVoegelin:LW:76**:15 list Nora, Byabe, Kizolo as dialects of Nung (which has an entry Nung [nun]).  Indeed,
fieldwork confirms Nung in China and Nung across the border in Myanmar are mutually intelligible (**hh:g:SunLiu:Anong**:8). See also: Nung (Myanmar) [nun].
